Rapper trio Quavious Marshall, 24, Kirschnick Ball, 20, and Kiari Cephus, 23, were escorted off Georgia Southern University campus mid-performance on Saturday night .
Authorities said they suspected the music stars were in possession of drugs when 'a very potent smell' of marijuana was detected coming from their two vans .
They reportedly face charges of drug possession and possession of firearms during the commission of a crime .